function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end

# Testing the function
@show timezone_bumper(DateTime(2023, 4, 10, 12, 0), 3)
```
This function receives a DateTime object and an integer number of hours to bump as input. It increases the DateTime by the number of hours specified in the bump argument and returns the new DateTime. If no bump value is provided, it defaults to 3 hours.
